'''Gary Gutting''' (born 1942) is an American philosopher and holder of an endowed chair in [[philosophy]] at the [[University of Notre Dame]].
==Work== Gutting is an expert on the philosopher [[Michel Foucault]] and an editor of ''[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]]''. Through his publications in such media outlets as ''[[The New York Times]]'' and [[The Stone (blog)|The Stone]], he has adopted the role of a public [[intellectual]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Bray |first=Christopher |date=2011-03-20 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2011/mar/20/thinking-impossible-philosopy-gary-gutting |title=Thinking the Impossible: French Philosophy Since 1960 by Gary Gutting – review |newspaper=[[The Observer]] |accessdate=2016-09-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |author= Richard Marshall |date= 2012-12-10 |url=http://www.3ammagazine.com/3am/what-philosophers-know/ |title=What Philosophers Know |magazine=[[3:AM Magazine]] |accessdate=July 7, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203041231/http://www.3ammagazine.com/3am/what-philosophers-know/ |archivedate=December 3, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/09/14/atheism-scientific-versus-humanist/ | publisher=Opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com | first=Gary | last=Gutting | title=Beyond 'New Atheism' | date=2011-09-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Gutting |first=Gary |url=https://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/08/11/on-dawkinss-atheism-a-response/ |title=The Stone: On Dawkins's Atheism: A Response |publisher=Opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com |date=2010-08-11 |accessdate=2011-10-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first=Gary | last=Gutting | url=https://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/08/01/philosophy-and-faith/ |title=The Stone: Philosophy and Faith | publisher=Opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com |date=2010-08-01 |accessdate=2011-10-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/05/22/why-do-i-teach/ | publisher=Opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com | first=Gary | last=Gutting | title=Why Do I Teach? | date=2013-05-22}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Douglas Smith |url=http://muse.jhu.edu/login?auth=0&type